<dl id="sd2748b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="nsd2" href="#sd2748b">SD2 (VI.A)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/sd2all.htm#sd2748b"> 748(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hystaspes</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font size="-1">BELSHAZZAR</font> ... The legends of Belshazzar&apos;s feast and of the siege and capture of Babylon by Cyrus which have come down to us from the book of Daniel and the <i>Cryopaedia</i> of Xenophon have been shown by the contemporaneous inscriptions to have been a projection backwards of the re-conquest of the city by Darius <mark>Hystaspis</mark>. The actual facts were very different. <small> &ldquo;BEELZEBUB&rdquo; <a name="EBBZ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBBZ"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 712</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
